## Project Workflow

### 1. Data Loading

* Loaded the dataset using Pandas.
* Explored dataset shape and structure.

### 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

* Checked missing values.
* Generated descriptive statistics.
* Visualized the distribution of house prices.
* Examined correlations between features.

### 3. Data Preprocessing

* Filled missing numerical values using the median.
* Filled missing categorical values using the mode.
* Removed unnecessary columns (e.g., `Id`).
* Applied One-Hot Encoding to categorical features.

### 4. Feature Selection

Important features influencing house prices include:

* Overall Quality
* Living Area
* Garage Capacity
* Basement Area
* Year Built
* Neighborhood
* Full Bathrooms

### 5. Model Building

* Split the dataset into training (80%) and testing (20%) sets.
* Trained a Linear Regression model.
* Trained a Ridge Regression model for comparison.

### 6. Model Evaluation

The model was evaluated using:

* Mean Squared Error (MSE)
* Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)
* R² Score

### 7. Data Visualization

* Distribution Plot of Sale Price
* Correlation Heatmap
* Actual vs Predicted Price Scatter Plot
* Residual Plot

### 8. Coefficient Analysis

Analyzed feature coefficients to determine which features have the highest positive and negative impact on house prices.

